genresAdvancedInfo.name: cambodian rock
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Cambodian rock is a genre that emerged in the 1960s and 1970s, blending traditional Khmer music with Western rock influences. It often features distorted guitar riffs, funky basslines, and soulful vocals, and was popularized by artists such as Sinn Sisamouth and Ros Sereysothea.
